Step 1: Install Prerequisites
Install Java
Install Kafka
Kafka requires Java to run. Install the latest Java Development Kit (JDK).
Download the JDK from Oracle's Java SE Downloads or Adoptium.
Install and set the JAVA_HOME environment variable:
Right-click This PC → Properties → Advanced system settings → Environment Variables.
Add a new System Variable:
Variable name: JAVA_HOME
Variable value: Path to the JDK (e.g., C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-17)
Add %JAVA_HOME%\bin to the Path variable.
CMD: java -version

Step 2: Download and Extract Kafka
Download Kafka from Kafka Downloads.
Select the latest version and download the binary for Scala 2.13.
Extract the downloaded .tgz file using a tool like 7-Zip into a folder, e.g., C:\kafka.
Download location: C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-3.9.0

